cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with language identification of cuneiform texts using automatic methods, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning algorithms for language identification, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries). The use of deep learning models for language identification could also place it under cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
